      'Stop cost-plus thinking. Start asking what value you create, rather than what it costs.'
    ],
    quote: {
      text: 'For early stage companies (pre PMF, less than €1M ARR) it is important that the CEO/Founder owns pricing. Plus to keep it iterative. Pricing V1 to win your first 10 customers, then Pricing V2 for the next 10-50.',
      author: 'Alexander Estner',
      role: 'Founder | GTM advisor for B2B SaaS startups'
    }
  },
  MLL: {
    code: 'MLL',
    name: 'The Tool Collectors',
    cls: 'Class 1',
    leakLo: 0.17, leakHi: 0.25,
    profile: 'You have pricing tools and processes, but still rely on gut pricing. There is some pricing infrastructure in place, and someone is probably nominally responsible for it. But the tools have not translated into better pricing decisions. The trap here is the illusion of progress: having the tools feels like having a system, but the output says otherwise.',
    moves: [
      'Clarify pricing ownership. One person, accountable for pricing performance.',
